title: For Sale:  Ruger American Predator .223
postcontent: For sale is one Ruger American Predator, chambered in .223, about 250 rounds through it. This thing is quite light almost to a fault, and being the Predator model it has the slightly thicker barrel with the threading on the end, and a picatiny rail section on the top. Stock has nice amount padding on the back too, so the .223 model is rather soft shooting. It's also stupidly accurate for a rifle at this price point, being sub-MOA with that 22in barrel that's free floated. It's even 1/8 twist, so it will shoot the heavier 62 and 69gr .223 bullets just fine. Trigger on the thing is unreal as well.My only problem is that the barrel is thin for the type of shooting I do, and I'd rather have a more dedicated precision rig. However, that tapered "bull barrel" and stock does make the rifle less than 7 pounds, so that's all an example of win some/ lose some. Not good for me, but for someone who appreciates a very light and accurate rifle that punches well above its price, it's great. Asking $325 for the rifle, but if you want the scope as well, then I'll throw that in for an extra $100. The scope is a Burris 2-7. Do need cash, so no trades.
